Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
index_collection(25.10)                                index_collection(25.10)

Name
       index_collection

Syntax
         index_collection

       [-help]

       <base_collection><index>

       Returns a collection containing the object that exists at the specified
       index of the specified object collection.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <base_collection>
              Specifies the base collection.

       <index>
              Specifies  the  index number. You can specify a number from 0 to
              <collection_size-1>.

Examples
              * The following command returns the object that  exists  at  the
                index number 2 in the object collection referenced by $nets:

                index_collection $nets 2

Related Information
              * append_to_collection

              * compare_collections

              * copy_collection

              * filter_collection

